- control flow is the order that we user to execute statements through our code
-conditionaal statements are used to check our code depending what information we want passed through
- if statements- if statementsare used to check data against one condition- ex: 

if(1 > 0){
    console.log(true)
}

-else if statements- the else if statement is used as when the if statment returns falsey "else" execute this code-
-ex-
if(n > 0){
    console.log(true)
}else if (n < 0){
    console.log(false)
}

-else statement-  else statements are usd to end your flow using one last condition meaning if none of this this execute this-
-ex-
if(n > 0){
    console.log(true)
}else if (n < 0){
    console.log(false)
}else {
    return 'who cares'
}

-switch statements- switch statements use cases to test data. if the case test comes back true then you 'break'
out of the statement- 
-ex-
switch (new Date().getDay()) {
  case 0:
    day = "Sunday";
    break;
  case 1:
    day = "Monday";
    break;
  case 2:
     day = "Tuesday";
    break;
  case 3:
    day = "Wednesday";
    break;
  case 4:
    day = "Thursday";
    break;
  case 5:
    day = "Friday";
    break;
  case 6:
    day = "Saturday";
}